{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "steve-krug",
    "senderColor": "cyan",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Ready for review, read all docs and CI config",
    "content": "Steve Krug here, ready for review. I've read PROJECT.md, TEAM_AGREEMENTS.md, and the current CI workflow (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`).\n\nCurrent state: CI already ignores `.claude-sessions/**` via `paths-ignore`. The proposal under discussion is to also skip CI when only docs/markdown files change.\n\nFrom a UX perspective, I'm supportive of this in principle. The team's workflow experience is itself a UX concern — unnecessary CI runs waste time and violate the \"CI wait rule\" (wait for green before pushing next commit). If a team member commits a glossary update or a product discovery doc change, waiting for a full build+test cycle adds friction to a non-code activity.\n\nI'll provide my full review once the specific proposal is shared. Standing by."
  }
}
